tasks.request:
When the supervisor encounters either of the situations below:
1) Error code: 401 - {'error': {'message': 'The API Key appears to be invalid or may have expired. Please verify your credentials and try again.', 'type': 'invalid_authentication_error'}}
2) Error code: 429 - {'error': {'message': "We're receiving too many requests at the moment. Please wait a moment and try again.", 'type': 'rate_limit_reached_error'}}
Phase 3 completion check: action? [1=keep (default), 2=revert, 3=other]:
It should automatically respond with "Proceed as you were" using similar functionality to how we automatically respond to the runner session when a CI gate failure is observed. This automatic response should happen regardless of when (e.g. all phases) this "error" occurs.
